One person was struck by lightning during the thunderstorm. According to the department, the unidentified dead person was with family members when the lightning struck, leaving some members with severe burns. Municipal spokesperson Mdu Dlamini yesterday said their disaster management team was on the ground and that more than eight families were affected by the storm. “The team was also helping families with food parcels, as well as blankets and tents for temporary shelter,” he said. Cogta spokesperson Lennox Mabaso said areas severely affected included Mbadleni under Jozini Municipality and Manaba under the uMhlabuyalingana Municipality, all in the north of the province. “We urge residents in the uMkhanyakude District to be cautious. Our KZN summer weather is one of extremes, where we experience high temperatures that can suddenly be replaced by violent storms,” he said. Daily News